            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Unknown declaration type - no children
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "visit_type_children" takes context as Integer, node as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Visit children of type nodes

    @Reasoning:
    Type nodes may have child types for:
    - Generic types: type parameters
    - Optional types: inner type
    - Array types: element type
    - Tuple types: component types
    - Union types: variant types
    - Function types: parameter and return types

    Every recursive visit_hir_node call is wrapped in the per-child
    triple (invoke_child_enter, visit_hir_node, invoke_child_exit). Null
    children are skipped entirely. Type-aware visitor consumers (future
    type checker, type unification, generic monomorphization) use the
    per-child hooks to drive substitution and constraint propagation.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation:
    HIRTypeInfo structure (from hir.runa):
    - offset 0: type_kind
    - offset 56: element_type (for Optional, Array)
    - offset 88: variant_types/component_types (for Union, Tuple)
    - offset 64: variant_count/component_count
    - offset 96: generic_params (for Generic)
    - offset 104: generic_count

    Child index assignment per type kind:
    - GENERIC: param i = child_index i (variadic)
    - OPTIONAL / ARRAY: inner/element = child_index 0
    - TUPLE / UNION: component i = child_index i (variadic)
    - FUNCTION: param i = child_index i, return_type = child_index param_count
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints:
    Type trees are typically shallow (most types are nullary or
    unary). The wide branch on type_kind selects the correct
    structural reader in O(1); variadic kinds (Generic, Tuple,
    Union, Function) iterate a fixed-count loop with no allocation.
    Type-checker consumers benefit because the per-child hooks let
    them push/pop substitution frames without re-walking the tree.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope:
    Null-node guard short-circuits before any field read. Each
    variadic loop is bounded by the count field stored in the node,
    so a corrupt list pointer cannot cause an over-read - the worst
    case is a missed child, flagged by validate_hir_tree downstream.
    Type kinds outside the recognized set fall through to a no-op
    return, matching the defensive policy used in every per-category
    visitor in this file.
    @End Security_Scope

